      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. but aren't there cases where a shared national identity is actually what keeps a diverse society from falling apart? like, without some level of nationalism, wouldn't it be harder to have social trust or even just a sense of duty to the community? it feels like you're saying any form of it is automatically bad.",
