      "content": "i get that, but it feels like you're still being a bit dismissive of the \"nationalism\" label itself. if we're talking about the actual movement or the belief that a nation's interests should come first, isn't that fundamentally different from just \"celebrating culture\"? it seems like you're trying to redefine what people mean when they actually use the word nationalism to make it sound more acceptable. shouldn't we look at the ideology on its own terms rather than just trying to sanitize it?",
